  "title": "The Uriel Ventris Chronicles Vol. 1 Omnibus",
  "synopsis": "The first three Uriel Ventris novels under Black Library's later 'Chronicles' reissue branding — Nightbringer, Warriors of Ultramar, and Dead Sky, Black Sun — content unchanged from the older Ultramarines Omnibus. A 4th Company captain learning what command costs: Ventris is sent first to the mercantile world of Pavonis with Inquisitor Ario Barzano on a corruption-and-conspiracy thread; then to the agri-world of Tarsis Ultra, where the Mortifactors and Imperial Guard hold the line against a Tyranid splinter-fleet; finally on a death-oath into the Eye of Terror itself, to Medrengard, where Honsou's Daemonculaba forges parody-Astartes and the Iron Warriors enter the saga. The canonical entry-point omnibus for the Ventris career.",
